A team consists of four players that all reside in one country.</p><br/><br/>


<h2>Results</h2>
<p>The winners of the Country tournament was The Netherlands starring: Albert "ANO" Nomden, Dirk "D K" Klaver, Mark "MVG" Vanderguten, and Paul "PFJ" Jongma! The second place was nicked by the USA, 3rd by Spain, and 4th by France.</p><br/><br/>


<h2>Qualifying</h2>
<p>
The teams will be divided into groups, <span class="changes">most probably three groups with four teams in each</span>. In each group, all the teams will face each other once. A match between two teams consists of the following games:
<br/><br/>
1.	First there will be a single game on a single machine in which all four players of each team participate. The machine will be set up for 4 balls per game and a &rdquo;two-player game&rdquo; will be started; each player of each team will play one single ball in this game. Players of the same team are allowed to coach each other during the game. The team with the highest score will receive 5 points, the losing team 0 points
<br/><br/>
2.	Second there will be two four-player games on two different machines (3 balls/game), played at the same time. In each game two players from each team will participate. The teams are allowed to change the lineup in each round of the competition; two players will play as players 1 and 3 on one machine, the other two play as players 2 and 4 on the other machine. Players will receive points as follows: the player with the highest score gets 9 points, second gets 5 points, third gets 2 points and fourth will get 0 points.
<br/><br/>
Players of the same team (pair) are allowed to coach each other during the game. Players of the other pair and the opponent team may not interfere with gameplay.
<br/><br/>
The total score of a match between two teams will be determined by adding up all the points gathered by the team members during the three games. The team with the most game points will receive 2 tournament/match points, the other team will receive 0 points.
<br/><br/>
After all group matches have been played, the best teams in each group will proceed to the semi-finals; ranking order will be determined by the total number of tournament points received. If two or more teams teams end up with the same number of points, the total amount of gamepoints will decide their positions.  If this is also equal the result in the match between the teams will decide.</p><br/><br/>


