<h2>Playoffs</h2>

<p><span class="changes">Each semi-final is played between two teams. The semi-finals are to be played in the same way as the qualification rounds, with the addition that the teams, starting with the group winners, will choose one machine each which will then be played on in the second part of the semi-final.</span><br/><br/>

The winners of the semi-finals will proceed to the final. The two battling teams will choose two machines each which will then be played on in the final. On each of the four machines a four-player game will be played (two matches at a time). Each team may decide which two players play on which machine. Players will receive points as follows: the player with the highest score gets 9 points, second gets 5 points, third gets 2 points and fourth will get 0 points. The total score will be determined by adding up all the points gathered by the team members during the two games. If the two teams end up with the same number of points a playoff game will be played; a single two-player game on a 4-ball machine in which each team member plays one ball.<br/><br/>

Machines will be set up on factory defaults with the following exceptions:
<br/>
<ul>
<li>4 balls per game (during the first step in the qualifying matches)</li>
<li>Tournament mode</li>
<li>No extra balls</li>
</ul>
</p>